title: Grateful Dead Live at Glens Falls Civic Center on 1979-08-31
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Dire Wolf, Cassidy, Loser, El Paso, Peggy-O, Minglewood Blues, Easy To Love You, Althea, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Deal

Set 2

Shakedown Street, Greatest Story Ever Told, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Around & Around

reviews.review_text:
Overlooked hot one I think many of us overlooked this show because 79 has so many other great shows. Not that I would call this one great but is still darn good. 1st Saint of circumstance. And only a handful of sailors before this night. Also Althea is brand new with it to only being played few times previously .
 Sound is pretty good here also, love the 79 Not fades they have different flair to them. This Althea has such a nice bouncy feel to it. Vocals are crystal clear.

 So considering this show has not been talked about much over the years I say it is a 4.5 for sound and creativity. 
Check it out folks you will be glad you did.

I like this one This may not be the greatest show of the year, but it was a great one to be at. I've been looking for a good copy of this one, and I'm glad I found this recording.

At the time, this seemed like the greatest Shakedown ever. On tape, it's really funky, but I can't say it's the best ever. I really love this version of Greatest Story.

The rest is just solid.
